-- World Energy Demand to Rise 40% by 2030, Chevron’s Kirkland Says
-- B y   D i n a k a r   S e t h u r a m a n
-- 2012-06-06T01:02:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/world-energy-demand-to-rise-40-by-2030-chevron-s-kirkland-says.html
Global energy demand will climb by 40
percent by 2030, George Kirkland,  Chevron Corp. (CVX) ’s upstream vice
president for gas, said today in  Kuala Lumpur .  From 2010 to 2030, Chevron sees worldwide gas consumption
rising by 60 trillion cubic feet a year, said Kirkland. There
are now 29 regasification projects for liquefied natural gas
under construction globally, he said at the World Gas Conference
in the Malaysian capital.  Chevron will shift its production portfolio to 40 percent
gas by 2017 from 30 percent now, said Kirkland.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in Kuala Lumpur at 
